Class OidList

java.lang.Object
  com.threerings.presents.dobj.OidList
All Implemented Interfaces:
Streamable, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Integer>
public class OidList
extends java.lang.Object
implements Streamable, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Integer>

An oid list is used to store lists of object ids. The list will not allow duplicate ids. This class is not synchronized, with the expectation that all modifications of instances will take place on the dobjmgr thread.

  • Do not use an OidList to store a set of ints. OidList has special meaning inside of the dobj system, namely:
  • When an object is destroyed, its oid is automagically removed from any OidLists.
